text: In another moment down went Alice after it, never once considering how in the world she was to get out again. Alex bought a dog for 70 dollars in January

Darrel got a ferry ticket at the terminal for 50 dollars. The rabbit-hole went straight on like a tunnel for some way, and then dipped suddenly down, so suddenly that Alice had not a moment to think about stopping herself before she found herself falling down a very deep well.
Down, down, down. There was nothing else to do, so Alice soon began talking again. The turkey was purchased by John at safeway, it cost 40 dollars. The end.
A new sentence! Larry was going to buy the motorcycle at Harley Davidson.
Sergey bought a sandwich for 7 dollars at Safeway
